From af809e72867313aabd7e8ba438fa395d7935c525 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 06:21:43 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 47/65] media: rockchip: rga: fix RGA3 scheduler error message

Plain-language impact:
A probe failure in the RGA3 scheduler path now reports RGA3, not RGA2.

Kernel details:
Correct the pr_err() string in the RGA3 init_scheduler() switch default.

Source: split from patches/cleanup-draft after docs/11-bsp-audit.md verification.
Signed-off-by: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_drv.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_drv.c b/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_drv.c
index a620cb338908..dd67986c72ec 100644
--- a/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_drv.c
+++ b/drivers/video/rockchip/rga3/rga_drv.c
@@ -1331,7 +1331,7 @@ static int init_scheduler(struct rga_scheduler_t *scheduler,
 			scheduler->core = RGA3_SCHEDULER_CORE1;
 			break;
 		default:
-			pr_err("scheduler failed to match RGA2\n");
+			pr_err("scheduler failed to match RGA3\n");
 			return -EINVAL;
 		}
 
